title: Marvel News: Marvel Loves Keanu And The End Of June Re-Release For Avengers: Endgame
body:
Marvel News: Marvel Loves Keanu And The End Of June Re-Release For Avengers: Endgame

Credit: Roy Rochlin/Getty Images

The first half of 2019 has seen Keanu Reeves very busy.

In March, there was a first look at Duke Caboom – an Evel Knievel-like stunt motorcyclist character which Reeves is voicing for the upcoming Toy Story 4.

Then came news about Bill and Ted Face The Music, currently in production, then the first trailers for John Wick Chapter 3 – Parabellum made an appearance.

title: a month has passed
body:
and suddenly the FEELS of Endgame have sprung on me all over again

this time about the Science Bros

cf:

Tony and Bruce get reunited for the first time in years, and then immediately separated again

Tony comes back in -pieces-, physically and mentally, and his recovery/the Snap means everybody scatters to the 4 winds; have the two of them even seen each other for 5 years by the time they reunite for the Time Heist?

Tony, Bruce-Hulk, and Nat get one last hurrah together, even including some time to eat Chinese food and snuggle together, Bruce gets to venture his life for the sake of the universe

and We Win, We Win, But What Did It Cost? Pepper, Peter, Rhodey, Steve and Thor are visible at Tony’s side; 

but Bruce lost both Nat and Tony and didn’t get a proper goodbye with either of them.

tl;dr SOMEONE GO HUG BRUCE-HULK AND TAKE CARE OF HIM
